---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AnnouncementBar from '../components/AnnouncementBar.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="California Privacy Notice | Hamilton Exteriors"
  description="California privacy notice for Hamilton Exteriors. Learn about your rights under the CCPA and how we handle your personal information."
  noindex
>
  <AnnouncementBar slot="header" />
  <Navbar slot="header" />

  <section class="w-full bg-cream py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-5">
      <h1 class="font-display text-[36px] leading-tight font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)] md:text-[48px]">
        California Privacy Notice
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-8 font-dm-sans text-base/relaxed text-gray-700">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: March 2026</p>

        <p>This California Privacy Notice is provided by Hamilton Exteriors, Inc. in compliance with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and the California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA). It explains what personal information we collect, how we use it, and what rights you have as a California resident.</p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">Personal Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>When you interact with our website, request an estimate, or engage our services, we may collect the following categories of personal information:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> Your name, email address, phone number, and mailing address</li>
          <li><strong>Project information:</strong> Details about your property, project scope, roof measurements, photos of your home, and service preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Commercial information:</strong> Records of services purchased, estimates requested, and payment history</li>
          <li><strong>Internet activity:</strong> Browsing history on our website, pages visited, and interactions with our online tools (such as our roof scanner)</li>
          <li><strong>Geolocation data:</strong> General location based on your IP address, or your property address when you use our roof scanning tool</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the personal information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Providing services:</strong> To prepare estimates, schedule consultations, plan projects, and complete the work you've hired us for</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to your inquiries, provide project updates, send appointment reminders, and follow up after project completion</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> To send you information about our services, promotions, or seasonal maintenance tips (you can opt out at any time)</li>
          <li><strong>Website improvement:</strong> To analyze how visitors use our website so we can improve the experience</li>
          <li><strong>Legal compliance:</strong> To comply with applicable laws, regulations, and contractor licensing requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">We Do Not Sell Your Personal Information</h2>
        <p>Hamilton Exteriors does not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. We do not share your information for cross-context behavioral advertising. We may share information with service providers who help us operate our business (such as payment processors or scheduling software), but only as needed to provide our services to you, and under contracts that protect your information.</p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">Your Rights as a California Resident</h2>
        <p>Under the CCPA and CPRA, you have the following rights:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Right to know:</strong> You can request that we disclose what personal information we have collected about you, where we got it, why we collected it, and who we've shared it with.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to delete:</strong> You can request that we delete the personal information we have collected about you, subject to certain exceptions (such as information needed to complete a transaction or comply with legal obligations).</li>
          <li><strong>Right to correct:</strong> You can request that we correct inaccurate personal information we maintain about you.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to opt out of sale or sharing:</strong> While we do not sell or share your personal information, you have the right to direct us not to do so.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to non-discrimination:</strong> We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your privacy rights. You will receive the same quality of service and pricing regardless of whether you exercise these rights.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">How to Exercise Your Rights</h2>
        <p>To make a request regarding your personal information, you can contact us using any of the following methods:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@hamilton-exteriors.com" class="text-primary underline">support@hamilton-exteriors.com</a> (include "Privacy Request" in the subject line)</li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+16509773351" class="text-primary underline">(650) 977-3351</a></li>
          <li><strong>Mail:</strong> Hamilton Exteriors, Inc., 21634 Redwood Rd Unit F, Castro Valley, CA 94546</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We will verify your identity before processing your request to protect your information. We will respond to verifiable requests within 45 days of receipt. If we need more time (up to an additional 45 days), we will notify you of the extension and the reason for it.</p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this notice, comply with our legal obligations (including contractor licensing and warranty record-keeping requirements), resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. Project records are typically retained for the duration of applicable warranty periods.</p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">Changes to This Notice</h2>
        <p>We may update this California Privacy Notice from time to time. When we make changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this notice periodically.</p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-[24px] font-bold text-[rgb(28,28,28)]">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this California Privacy Notice or our privacy practices, please contact us:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+16509773351" class="text-primary underline">(650) 977-3351</a></li>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@hamilton-exteriors.com" class="text-primary underline">support@hamilton-exteriors.com</a></li>
          <li><strong>Mail:</strong> Hamilton Exteriors, Inc., 21634 Redwood Rd Unit F, Castro Valley, CA 94546</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="w-full bg-white py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[600px] px-5 text-center">
      <p class="font-dm-sans text-base text-gray-600">
        Have questions about our services?
      </p>
      <a
        href="/"
        class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-primary px-8 py-3 font-dm-sans text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-primary/90"
      >
        Back to Home
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>
